  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Starting when you choose this tradition at 3rd level, you can use your Ki to duplicate the effects of certain spells. As an action, you can spend 2 ki points to cast @UUID[Compendium.materia-dnd.spells.Item.sApWByvBq5cL3ZoG]{Darkness}, @UUID[Compendium.materia-dnd.spells.Item.eP8ZCXxlGFJzKIUz]{Pass without Trace}, or @UUID[Compendium.materia-dnd.spells.Item.TsXoAnsMto2MIufg]{Silence} without providing material components. Additionally, you gain the @UUID[Compendium.materia-dnd.spells.Item.n0Bo39iWm09h4Iqq]{Minor Illusion}cantrip and Wisdom is your spellcasting ability for it if you do not already know the cantrip.</p><ul><li><p>You are able to see within the are of your darkness spell when you use ki to cast it.</p></li><li><p>As an action at the start of your turn you can move your darkness, minor illusion, or silence spell to a space within 60 feet of you.</p></li><li><p>You gain darkvision out to a range of 60 feet. If you already have darkvision, its range increases by 60 feet.</p></li></ul><p>Starting at 6th level in this class, you can see in magical darkness even if it is not your own.</p><blockquote><p><strong>Upon getting this feature, you should drag the above spells onto your character sheet to add them to your spell list, and set the Spellcasting Ability for each to Wisdom. You will need to manually expend ki points or spell slots to cast them still, however.</strong></p></blockquote>",
